      "representative_excerpt": "\u201d This change is scientifically inaccurate, ethically concerning, and carries the potential for unintended consequences in commercial harvesting and trade. 1. Biological inaccuracy Octopuses, squid, and cuttlefish are Cephalopoda, a class of mollusks that lack external shells. Classifying them as shellfish misrepresents their taxonomy and ignores established...",
