      "representative_excerpt": "The term \u201cshellfish\u201d has a well-established meaning in both scientific and common usage. It typically refers to aquatic invertebrates with shells, such as clams, oysters, mussels, and crustaceans like shrimp and crab. Cephalopods are biologically distinct from these organisms. Although they are mollusks, most cephalopods lack an external shell and possess ve...",
